theorem isClosed_P3_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed A → Topology.P3 A → IsOpen A := by
  intro hClosed hP3
  -- First, show that `A ⊆ interior A`
  have h_sub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    intro x hx
    have : x ∈ interior (closure A) := hP3 hx
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq] using this
  -- Hence, `A = interior A`
  have h_eq : (A : Set X) = interior A := subset_antisymm h_sub interior_subset
  -- Use the fact that `interior A` is open
  simpa [h_eq] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A))

theorem P1_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P1 (∅ : Set X) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  cases hx
